Class PostService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nitor.dux.common.service.RestService
      • com.nitor.iugo.po.serviceobjects.AppRestService
        • com.nitor.iugo.po.serviceobjects.PostService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.nitor.dux.common.service.IServiceClient

    public class PostService
extends AppRestService
    PostService shows the page object of JSON PlaceHolder API. This service is used to imitate JSON REST api and returns mock objects. Its not real service. The intention here is to guide user on creating page objects of services-under-test. Constructor here only consists of setting url and not accessing RestConfiguration object as this object doesnt require to access that. But user should feel free on setting/accessing RestConfiguration object like done in GooglePlacesXmlService

    anup.manekar
